# Netlify deploy (book-gallery)

When deploying **this** project to production:

- Run from the repo root: `npx netlify-cli deploy --prod --dir .`
- Ensure the folder is linked to **`lewiscooklibrary`** (`npx netlify-cli status`).

Do **not** tell the user to rely only on **Netlify UI → Trigger deploy** unless **GitHub `main` already contains** the same changes: UI deploys build from Git, while CLI deploy uploads the **local** tree. If local work is not pushed, UI deploys can drop features.

After meaningful changes, prefer **git push** so Git and CLI stay aligned, then CLI deploy is still fine.
